>>Why is benchmarking important?||Please choose 3 options.||<<

[x] A. To compare models to each other {{selected: A. Correct, different models’ performance can be assessed relative to each other on various tasks.}}
[x] B. To define what “better” means for models {{selected: B. Correct, given the variety of tasks, a “better” model will often outperform others on a certain set of tasks, not on every task imaginable. }}
[ ] C. To see how well models would perform if deployed in the real world {{selected: B. Incorrect, benchmarking takes place on open-source, highly curated datasets. They are not used to assess model performance in deployment.}}
[x] D. To understand the tradeoffs between performance on various tasks and training time {{selected: C. Correct, by comparing model performance versus time spent training, a new dynamic is considered: should training time be constrained, which model performs best? }}

